// TEST: Float Division Of Whole-Valued Literals
// ============================================================================
// REGRESSION (pre-AD literal fix): %g rendered 2.0 as the bare token `2`, an
// int literal in C++, so `2.0 / 3.0` compiled to integer division and
// evaluated to 0. Float literals must always be SPELLED floating in the
// generated C++ (trailing .0 when the value is whole).
// ============================================================================
let twothirds = 2.0 / 3.0
let half = 1.0 / 2.0
let mixed = 3.0 / 2
// EXPECT: twothirds = 0.6666666666666666
// EXPECT: half = 0.5
// EXPECT: mixed = 1.5
